FBIS4-51463 "drchi103_w_94022" FBIS-CHI-94-103 Daily Report 25 May 1994 HONG KONG & MACAO Macao Official Addresses Enterprise Association Official Addresses Enterprise Association OW2605203994 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1421 GMT 25 May 94 OW2605203994 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service Chinese BFN [By reporter Wang Zhigeng (3769 1807 5087)] [Text] Macao, 25 May (XINHUA) -- Guo Dongpo, director of the Macao Branch of XINHUA NEWS AGENCY, delivered a speech at the second general membership meeting of the Association of Chinese Enterprises today. He hoped that the Association of Chinese Enterprises will make new contributions to Macao's smooth transition and economic prosperity. Guo Dongpo said that in the two years and more since its founding, the Association of Chinese Enterprises of Macao has done a great deal of effective work to promote economic relations and trade between Macao and the mainland, as well as economic cooperation and trade between the two and other countries and regions. It has played an important role in promoting social stability, progress, and economic development in Macao. Guo Dongpo called on the Association to continue to, as before, take an active part in Macao affairs during the transitional period, enhance its sense of urgency and historic responsibility, work with one heart and one mind, and make new contributions to Macao's smooth transition and to the motherland's four modernizations. Zhang Xuming, president of the Association of Chinese Enterprises of Macao, said in his speech that in the days to come, the Association of Chinese Enterprises of Macao will offer even better coordination and service among its members and continue to work hard for Macao's economic prosperity. The Association of Chinese Enterprises of Macao, set up on 3 April 1992, now has 155 members. Zhang Xuming was reelected the president of the association during the current general membership meeting.
